    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hi, i'm looking at some high protein dog food for my lab, he's getting up there in age (about 9). i noticed the protein is pretty high but i'm worried about the fat content and how it affects him long term. what's a good protein to fat ratio for an older lab?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an older Labrador, a well-balanced protein to fat ratio is key for maintaining muscle mass without causing weight issues. Generally, look for meals with adequate protein (around 25-30%) but moderate fat, aiming for around a 12-18% fat level. Always prioritize high-quality, digestible ingredients over just the raw numbers on the label. If you have concerns, discussing specific formulations with your veterinarian is the safest approach.",
      "source": "target",
