    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'm also looking at the ingredients list and i see some stuff like \"animal by-products\" and \"meat meal\". do those matter a lot for his digestion or is it just filler? also how much extra fat should i be worried about if he's not as active as he used to be?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "While \"meat meal\" and \"by-products\" are protein sources, their quality varies significantly, so check if they come from recognizable animal parts. If these ingredients are listed early, they are major components, but overall quality matters more than the vague term itself. Since your Lab is less active, you should be more mindful of excess calories from fat; a higher fat content can easily lead to weight gain in less active senior dogs.",
      "source": "target",
